HEADWORD: Rheophore
<hw>Rhe"o*phore</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧"⟦osl⟧*f⟦omac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>"rei^n</grk> to flow + <?/<?/<?/ to carry.]</ety>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A connecting wire of an electric or
voltaic apparatus, traversed by a current.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One
of the poles of a voltaic battery; an electrode.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

